title: French Montana Lives It Up With Chris Brown and Migos in New Video for "Hold Up"
text:
French Montana Lives It Up With Chris Brown and Migos in New Video for "Hold Up" By Edwin Ortiz Edwin Ortiz is the news editor for Complex Music​. Follow @iTunesEra .
 Subscribe to Complex Video via YouTube You can always count on French Montana to randomly pop up with a street single featuring some big name friends, and that's the case today as the Bronx rapper links up with Chris Brown and Migos for "Hold Up." The track dropped alongside the video, which features Montana, Brown, as well as with Migos members Quavo and Takeoff turning up backstage and on the tour bus with their respective crews.
French looks to be building back his buzz that took a slight hit with the somewhat tumultuous release schedule of MC4 , and "Hold Up" is a step in the right direction, even if the video leaves little to the imagination. Meanwhile, Migos are currently enjoying a hot streak off the strength of their album Culture and its chart-topping single "Bad and Boujee." And Chris Brown, well, he's dealing with some issues outside of music that sound pretty serious .
